Define the `DeriveHandler` trait that computed fields implement to support both read (compute) and write (apply) operations.

## Trait definition

```rust
pub trait DeriveHandler: Send + Sync {
    /// Compute the field value from the entity (read path)
    fn compute(&self, entity: &Entity, schema: &EntityDef) -> Value;
    /// Apply a desired value by mutating the entity (write path)
    fn apply(&self, entity: &mut Entity, schema: &EntityDef, desired: &Value) -> Result<()>;
    /// Whether this computed field is writable (default: true)
    fn writable(&self) -> bool { true }
}
```

Add a `DeriveRegistry` that maps derive rule strings (e.g. `"parse-body-tags"`) to `Box<dyn DeriveHandler>` instances.

